                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18430403-1389-offence-1 t18430403-name-1502"></join>Edward Towill</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430403-name-1503" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1503" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1503" type="surname" value="WALTERS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1503" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>MARY WALTERS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopwoman to Edward Towell, of the Borough. The prisoner has been his shopman, on and off, for four or five years—on the 1st of March he was in the shop with me—the woman who usually brings his dinner, came in about half-past eleven o'clock with a basket—she set it on the further side of the counter, on a chair, and came and talked to me—I saw the prisoner cross the shop, take some boots off a nail, and put them on the end of the counter—I afterwards missed them—I saw the prisoner shuffling about at the bottom of the counter, and thought something was not right—he took up the basket, and was handing it to the woman—he said, "You may as well take this basket home now"—I said, "No, you don't take it out till I have looked at it"—I looked into it, and found a pair of Blucher-boots and a pair of Wellington's, which are here—they are my master's property—I took them out of the basket, told the woman to go out of the shop directly, and told the prisoner also to go—I did not see him again till he was in cus<lb></lb>tody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430403-name-1504" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1504" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
